<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
Rudolph A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Philippi’s">Philippi's</normalizedToken>
description of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium chrysanthum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysanthum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium chrysanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Linnaea" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 308" refId="B36" refString="Philippi, RA, 1864. Plantarum novarum Chilensium. Linnaea 33: 1 - 308" title="Plantarum novarum Chilensium." volume="33" year="1864">Philippi 1864</bibRefCitation>
) was based on material collected by H. Volckmann near Illapel, Chile. 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
indicated a specimen housed at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
. However, two sheets linked to 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. chrysanthum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="chrysanthum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E. chrysanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were located at SGO and, therefore, his statement must be considered as a first-step lectotypification. In order to narrow this broad designation, the specimen SGO000004051 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
